<div id="Idea_4146"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4146-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4146">Welfair Reform/ Food Stamps!&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/9349-4049">Lewis Foster</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">I have been running a 7-11 type C-Store for 16 years. I get 300.00 - 600.00 a day in Food Stamps. They buy Fountain drinks (Without the Straw, it's Fast food with the straw. STUPID) and get mad when my employees tell them to remove the straw. They buy the most Expenisive things I carry all of it Junk Food, Candy, Chips, Coke, Cakes. I can't afford Evian Water, but they can. Why! can't Food Stamps be just for food? a Fountain Drink is not Food... That would cut down a lot of the Overweight people I see everyday. The Gov. has a chart on what sould be eaten and how much per day. use this as a guideline on what can be bought. They should be instructed not to buy the MOST costly Items. Stores can be set up to sell only the most cost effective Items. It would take no time to set up this system. <br/>The Fraud in the Welfair system is out of control and I see it EVERYDAY. It's costing Billions every year..<br/></div>
