<a href="/akira/dtd/4132-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4132">Make a mix (public and private) health care system,  just like in France&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/9838-4049">Vicky Rodgers</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Here is the way it works:<br/>The government insures you against diseases.  You have a choice of all sorts of private insurance for any budget and any need.  There are moderators tickets (paid by government if you are poor, paid by the private insurance if you have one) at emergencies room.<br/><br/>If you are sick, you can choose your type of hospital: public, private non-profit or private.<br/><br/>PS: In Canada, health care is managed by the Province, not the federal government...</div>
