<div id="Idea_4125"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4125-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4125">The GITMO Solution&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/8469-4049">longshot9999</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">It seems like people think the question of what to do with the prisoners being held at Guatanamo is a lot harder to answer than it really is.  Prisoner exchanges have taken place for centuries with no negative impact on the reputation of the countries involved.  While it's understood that the prisoners you're trading will probably try to attack you again, it's also understood by your enemies that the prisoners you're receiving in return will try to attack them.  If no one's hold any prisoners we'd like to get back at the moment then we could always bolster our relationship with our allies by offerring to trade these prisoners for some of their men that are being held captive.  Since our allies are fighting the same people we are it would be a win-win situation all around.  And GITMO would be gone. </div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_4125" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_4125', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2255&topicID=4125')">Comments (0)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_4125"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2255">Uncategorized</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=guantanamo">guantanamo</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=al-qaida">al-qaida</a>,&nbsp;<a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?mode=tag&tag=terrorism">terrorism</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_4125"></div>
