<a href="/akira/dtd/4108-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4108">Executive Pay&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/9191-4049">pecohen</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">Most executive pay is by stock options and stock grants.  This is fine and should be encouraged, but these stock options and grants need a condition placed on them.  Specifically, they should not be negotiable until at least five years after the executive has left the company employment.</div>
