<div id="Idea_4085"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4085-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4085">Stop switching the time of day two times a year&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/8938-4049">sally</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">The switching of time causes tremendous stress on everyone. Those who like the long evenings of daylight should just adjust their work schedule. I know of not one parent or teacher who thinks changing the time is good for their children. It is hell on farms- especially dairies who have to suddenly milk the cows at a different time to make the milk deliveries.<br/><br/>Please just pick one time for each zone and stick with it. </div>
